"Badoglian" is an adjective describing those [[Italian]] soldiers who chose to stay faithful to the Italian Crown and then-Army Commander [[General Badoglio|Pietro Badoglio]] after [[w:September 8]] [[w:1943]], during [[w:World War II]], as the [[Fascism|Fascist]] regime fell in [[Italy]] and the Italian army was left without a lead as [[King Victor Emmanuel III|Victor Emmanuel III of Italy]] fled the country.